The paper deals with signal recovery on graphs, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data science (cs.DS). The use of experimentally designed sampling also suggests a possible connection to scientific computing (cs.NA). The focus on smooth graph signals and the proposed recovery strategies further suggest a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SI).
